article.headline: UC Davis 70, N. Arizona 65
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Harrison DuPont scored a career-high 19 points off the bench and UC Davis rallied from 21 points down to beat Northern Arizona 69-65 on Saturday night. Paolo Mancasola hit a pair of tiebreaking free throws with 2:36 left and DuPont scored the Aggies' final seven points to help UC Davis (4-22) snap a 15-game road losing streak. Durrell Norman scored a career-high 26 points for the Lumberjacks (5-22), who led 41-20 late in the first half. Gaellan Bewernick added 14 points and 13 rebounds for Northern Arizona, which has lost 14 straight. The game was part of the BracketBusters series.
